The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of an explanation algorithm for image classification applications of CNNs, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) aspects. Therefore, cs.HC is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) topics, as it discusses the performance of CNNs and their operation. Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (NLP) briefly, which falls under the cs.CL sub-category. Finally, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category, as the paper deals with explainable AI and its implications for design and further research.
